    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i get that there are different views, but is it really \"mixed\" though? it feels like if you look at the actual data on recidivism and how these laws affect community trust, the \"tough on crime\" approach is pretty much proven to be a failure. isn't it basically just outdated at this point?",
