    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "so if it's \"insufficient\" and \"fails\" to prevent crime, then why do people still keep pushing for it? is it just because they don't care about the social impact, or is there actually some real merit to the deterrence argument that i'm missing? be real with me, is it even a valid strategy anymore?",
